o-CTs with a mean\nabsolute error of 109.8 +/- 13.0 HU across the whole head and 319.3 +/- 31.9 HU\nin the skull. In acoustic simulations, the focal pressure was statistically\nequivalent for simulations based on reference CT and pseudo-CT (0.48 +/- 0.04\nMPa and 0.50 +/- 0.04 MPa respectively) but not for binary skull masks (0.28\n+/- 0.05 MPa).\n  Conclusions: We show that our network can produce pseudo-CT comparable to\nreference CTs in healthy individuals, and that these can be used in acoustic\nsimulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 24 Sep 2022 15:23:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-27"}
